cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper presents a novel approach to recurrent neural network regularization for natural language processing (NLP) benchmarks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new regularization method for neural networks. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as the paper focuses on recurrent neural networks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a broad category that could also apply as the paper presents a new approach to improve the performance of neural networks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the proposed method could potentially be applied to recurrent neural networks used in computer vision tasks.
